news.title: Pune: Maha Metro told to 'cover' Swargate concrete mix plant, prevent pollution
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) administrator Vikram Kumar said, “Precautionary measures need to be taken within three days of receiving the notice. The PMC may consider giving a stop-work order, if the Metro fails to take action within the stipulated time.”

news.title: Cement companies poised for stronger show in H2 FY24
news.para: The improved profitability in the September quarter, along with the expected improvement in the December and March quarters is expected to lift the average operating profit per tonne of cement makers to ₹970 per tonne in FY24 compared with ₹745 per tonne a year ago, Axis Securities said in a note.

news.title: Complete houses by February 2024, Andhra Pradesh CM tells officials
news.para: At a review meeting on housing on Thursday, the chief minister said the official machinery should act in such a way that identified problems are solved immediately.

news.title: Just three out of 116 Chandigarh housing board properties sold
news.para: The CHB had floated e-tenders to auction 116 freehold residential and leasehold commercial properties. Three residential freehold properties were sold and not a single bidder for 88 leasehold commercial properties came forward.

news.title: SEIAA to check compliance of projects cleared in last two years in Delhi
news.para: SEIAA, which grants clearance to any project on certain conditions, said the decision has been taken as there is currently no process to check if project proponents were complying with the conditions mentioned in the EC.

news.title: Gurugram: Violated building plans, owners of 19 flats in M2K society served DTCP notices
news.para: The move came after the enforcement team of the department received complaints via the CM window about illegal constructions on terrces, ground floors and balconies of some flats.

news.title: Edelweiss Alternatives aims to raise up to Rs 5,000 crore via rental yield fund
news.para: The fund will primarily target markets in southern India such as Bengaluru and Hyderabad, alongside major markets like Delhi-NCR and Mumbai, with plans to build a 10-million-sq-ft portfolio within three years.

news.title: Realty prices in Mumbai may rocket on back of Dharavi revamp TDR
news.para: Property market sources fear real estate prices in Mumbai may shoot up once TDR from the Dharavi revamp project becomes available.

news.title: Bombay HC declines to grant relief in slum's Rs 15 crore transit rent plea
news.para: HC was hearing a petition by Vaibhavi SRA Cooperative Housing Society Ltd against a March 2023 status quo order by the apex grievance redressal committee (AGRC).

news.title: Noida authority announces two commercial plot allocation schemes
news.para: The registration process for commercial builder plots ranging from 812.73 sq m to 51,417.25 sq m has started under the new plot allocation scheme.

news.title: Brigade Group to develop over 14 acres land in Yelahanka, Bengaluru
news.para: Brigade Group's project will have a developable area of around two million sq ft of residential housing with a gross development value (GDV) of Rs. 2,100 crore

news.title: China: Court auction to sell Shimao Group's land in Shenzhen fails again
news.para: Twelve land plots totalling 243,602 square metres, together with some uncompleted buildings on them, have asked for 10.4 billion yuan ($1.4 billion), 20% lower than the 13 billion yuan starting price in the first auction in July, according to e-commerce company JD.com's online auction platform.

news.title: Canadian home sales post biggest decline in 16 months in October
news.para: Canadian home sales fell 5.6% in October from September, the fourth straight month of declines and the biggest since June 2022. On an annual basis, without adjustment for seasonal variation, sales were up 0.9%.

news.title: Six months on, PWD's smart streetlight project yet to start in Delhi
news.para: The policy was approved in June by chief minister Arvind Kejriwal, with an aim to reduce electricity consumption and find a way to fix the problems with the conventional high-pressure sodium lights.

news.title: Religare Housing Finance looks to touch Rs 70-80 crore disbursal in FY24
news.para: Religare Housing Finance's book size is around Rs 255 crore net non-performing assets (NPA) is around 2.3 per cent and borrowing cost is in excess of around 12 per cent.

news.title: Kochi metro not to wait for decision on land acquisition
news.para: KMRL is planning to start the construction works of the other eight stations if the process of acquiring the land for Chembumukku and Padamugal stations are delayed.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body issues notices to 190 constructions sites
news.para: According to Chayya Dangale, public relation officer of Ulhasnagar Municipal Corporation, civic officials issued notices to 190 construction sites, reiterating the guidelines of the latest mitigation plans.

news.title: Kochi: Housing complex project to be ready by February 2024
news.para: The first housing complex is being constructed at Thuruthy. Kochi corporation is implementing the project with the financial support of Cochin Smart Mission Ltd (CSML).
